com.github.valid8j.pcond.forms

Class Predicates

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.valid8j.pcond.forms.Predicates

  • public class Predicates
extends Object

    An entry point for acquiring predicate objects. Predicates retrieved by methods in this class are all "printable".

      • callp

        public static <T> Predicate<T> callp(MethodQuery methodQuery)

        Returns a Predicate created from a method specified by a methodQuery. If the methodQuery matches none or more than one methods, a RuntimeException will be thrown.

        The suffix p stands for "predicate" following the custom in LISP culture and it is necessary to avoid collision with Functions.call( MethodQuery ) method.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the input to the returned predicate
        Parameters:
        methodQuery - A query object that specifies a method to be invoked by the returned predicate.
        Returns:
        Created predicate.
        See Also:
        Functions.classMethod(Class, String, Object[]), Functions.instanceMethod(Object, String, Object[]), Functions.parameter()

      • callp

        public static <T> Predicate<T> callp(String methodName,
                                     Object... arguments)

        Returns a predicate that calls a method which matches the given methodName and args on the object given as input to it.

        Note that method look up is done when the predicate is applied. This means this method does not throw any exception by itself and in case you give wrong methodName or arguments, an exception will be thrown when the returned function is applied.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of input to the returned predicate
        Parameters:
        methodName - The method name
        arguments - Arguments passed to the method.
        Returns:
        A predicate that invokes the method matching the methodName and args
        See Also:
        Functions.parameter()
